## Features

- Member Management: Register, log in, and manage member profiles.
- Event Promotion: Create, update, and promote upcoming movie events.
- Membership Handling: Purchase and manage club memberships with secure payment processing via Stripe.
- Interactive UI: A polished and responsive user interface built with Chakra UI.
- Real-time Data: Utilizes GraphQL for efficient data retrieval and manipulation.
- Secure Authentication: Implements JWT for secure user authentication.
- Mobile Responsive: Ensures a seamless experience across all devices.


## Installation

1. Clone the repo:
```
git clone https://github.com/Julian-A-Mort/Movie-Club-App
```

2. install the necessary dependencies (in both root, server and client directories)
```
npm install
```

3. Set up environmental variables for MongoDB URI, JWT secrets, Stripe API keys, and TMDB API key in .env files.

4. Start the server (in the root directory)

```
npm run start
```

## Technologies
Frontend: React.js with Chakra UI for styling
Backend: Node.js and Express.js server
Database: MongoDB with Mongoose ODM
APIs: TMDB for movie details, Stripe for payment processing
Authentication: JWT for secure login and session management

## Usage
After starting the application:

Visit http://localhost:3000 to view the client application.
Use the search bar to search for books.
Sign up/Log in to save books to your personal reading list.
View and delete books from your reading list.

## Deployment
This app is deployed on Render. Visit [https://goblin-movie-club-app.onrender.com/] to access the live application.

